  "text": "Empirical evidence suggests that repeatability often reflects heritable differences [CITATION_1] . However, long-lived animals can give transient positive repeatability during short-term studies [CITATION_2] . Furthermore, the high repeatability of spring departure dates could be parsimoniously explained by area-specific climatic and social effects, rather than by genetic variation among individuals.",
